Python cgi programming is a script which tells the browser to do after the user inputs or sees the html file.
CGI :
follow the following steps to create a python cgi file:
first create a python file this is your cgi python file, save it in the web server folder.
create a html form with <form   action = the name of the cgi python file   method = get (or) post> and save the file in the same web server folder.
open the cgi python file specified in the html file and type the program.
open the web server and activate it.
open the html file in the webserver and enter the inputs which is in the <form> tag.
open the cgi python file in the webserver and you can see the program you enterd is running.